	<TextInfo>
		<Text Type="Business Summary" lastModified="2015-07-17T04:19:39">Polar Capital Holdings plc is a United Kingdom-based investment management company. The Company offers professional and institutional investors a range of fundamental research-driven funds diversified by asset class, geographical and sectoral specialization. The Company provides research driven specialist investment products across long only, long bias, equity long/short and other fundamentally driven hedge fund strategies. Its subsidiaries include Polar Capital Partners Limited, Polar Capital Property Limited, Polar Capital Partners (Jersey) Limited, Polar Capital (America) Corporation and Polar Capital Limited Liability Partnership.</Text>
		<Text Type="Financial Summary" lastModified="2016-02-22T14:22:46">BRIEF: For the six months ended 30 September 2015, Polar Capital Holdings plc revenues increased less than 1% to L40.7M. Net income increased 2% to L9.2M. Revenues reflect Finance income increase from -L1.2M to L879K, Investment Performance Fees increase from L0K to L42K, also reflect Profit on forward currency contracts decrease from L516K to -L554K. Dividend per share remained flat at L0.06.</Text>
